# Human Design System — Agent Rules

## Typography

- **Canonical typeface**: Avenir (all platforms).
- Web (dashboard + website): use `var(--hu-font)` or `var(--hu-font-mono)`. Never set `font-family` directly.
- Apple native (iOS/macOS): use `Font.custom("Avenir-Book", size:)`, `Font.custom("Avenir-Medium", size:)`, `Font.custom("Avenir-Heavy", size:)`, `Font.custom("Avenir-Black", size:)`.
- Android: use `AvenirFontFamily` from `Theme.kt`. Never reference system fonts directly.
- **Never** import Google Fonts or any external font CDN.
- **Never** use raw `font-family:` declarations — always reference the design token.

## Icons

- **Canonical icon library**: Phosphor Regular.
- Web dashboard: import from `ui/src/icons.ts` — e.g. `import { icons } from '../icons.js'` then `${icons.house(20)}`.
- Website (Astro): use inline Phosphor SVGs with `viewBox="0 0 256 256" fill="currentColor"`.
- Native apps: use SF Symbols (Apple) or Material Icons (Android) where Phosphor equivalents are unavailable.
- **Never** use emoji characters (e.g. ⚠️, 💬, 🔧, ⚡, ⚙) as UI icons.
- **Never** create one-off inline SVGs when a Phosphor icon exists in the icon module.
- To add a new icon, add it to `ui/src/icons.ts` using Phosphor Regular paths with `viewBox="0 0 256 256"`.

## Design Tokens

- **Centralized design strategy**: `docs/standards/design/design-strategy.md` is the design constitution. Read it first.
- All values must reference `--hu-*` CSS custom properties from `design-tokens/`.
- **Never** use raw hex color values in CSS — use `var(--hu-accent)`, `var(--hu-text)`, etc.
- **Never** use raw pixel values for spacing — use `var(--hu-space-sm)`, `var(--hu-space-md)`, etc.
- **Never** use raw pixel values for border-radius — use `var(--hu-radius)`, `var(--hu-radius-lg)`, etc.
- Shadow values must use `var(--hu-shadow-sm)`, `var(--hu-shadow-md)`, `var(--hu-shadow-lg)`.
- Token namespace: `--hu-` prefix for all custom properties.
- **Lint enforcement**: Run `ui/scripts/lint-raw-values.sh` to check for drift. Wired into `npm run check`.

## Surfaces (M3 Tonal)

- **Tonal surfaces** use `--hu-surface-container`, `--hu-surface-container-high`, `--hu-surface-container-highest` for branded card/panel backgrounds
- Use tonal surfaces instead of `--hu-bg-surface` when the surface should carry brand identity
- Use `--hu-surface-dim` for recessed wells, `--hu-surface-bright` for hero/featured areas
- Plain `--hu-bg-surface` / `--hu-bg-elevated` remain available for neutral (non-tinted) surfaces
- **State layers** are primary-tinted: `--hu-hover-overlay`, `--hu-pressed-overlay`, `--hu-focus-overlay`, `--hu-dragged-overlay` all use human green
- `--hu-disabled-overlay` remains neutral (no brand color on disabled states)

## Glass

- Three tiers: `.hu-glass-subtle` (nav/chrome), `.hu-glass-standard` (cards/panels), `.hu-glass-prominent` (modals/sheets)
- Interactive glass: add `.hu-glass-interactive` for hover glow + press scale
- Tinted glass: add `.hu-glass-tinted` for accent-colored tint
- Enter/exit: use `.hu-glass-enter` / `.hu-glass-exit` for choreographed blur reveal
- Material densities: `--hu-glass-material-{ultra-thin,thin,regular,thick}-*` tokens (Apple visionOS-style)
- **Never** stack glass on glass without testing legibility
- All glass respects `prefers-reduced-transparency: reduce` fallback in `theme.css`
- Token source: `design-tokens/glass.tokens.json`

## Dynamic Color

- OKLCH palette auto-generated from brand hex `#7AB648` via `design-tokens/dynamic-color-lib.ts`
- Tokens: `--hu-dynamic-{primary,secondary,tertiary,neutral,error}-{50..950}`
- P3 wide-gamut overrides included automatically
- Generated CSS: `ui/src/styles/_dynamic-color.css` (imported by `theme.css`)
- To regenerate: `cd design-tokens && npm run build`
- To preview standalone: `npx tsx design-tokens/dynamic-color.ts --hex "#7AB648" --format css`

## Data Visualization

- Multi-series charts use `--hu-chart-categorical-{1..16}` in order. Never ad-hoc colors.
- Ordered data uses `--hu-chart-sequential-{100..800}` (Human green ramp).
- Positive/negative indicators use `--hu-chart-diverging-{positive,neutral,negative}`.
- Single-metric charts use `--hu-chart-brand`.
- Token source: `design-tokens/data-viz.tokens.json`.

## Motion & Animation

- Always use `var(--hu-duration-fast)`, `var(--hu-duration-normal)`, `var(--hu-duration-slow)` for timing.
- Always use `var(--hu-ease-out)`, `var(--hu-ease-in-out)` for easing.
- Use `var(--hu-ease-spring)` / `var(--hu-ease-spring-gentle)` for interactive elements (buttons, toggles, cards).
- Use `var(--hu-spring-out)` / `var(--hu-spring-bounce)` for CSS `linear()` spring approximations.
- Spring physics params (`--hu-spring-micro`, `--hu-spring-standard`, `--hu-spring-expressive`, `--hu-spring-dramatic`) for JS animation libs.
- **Every animation must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`**. Use the global media query in `theme.css` or add component-level `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` overrides.
- Keyframe names use `hu-` prefix (e.g. `hu-fade-in`, `hu-slide-up`).

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have visible focus rings using `--hu-accent`.
- Modals must trap focus and support Escape to close.
- Tooltips must be keyboard-accessible (show on focus, not just hover).
- Use semantic HTML and ARIA attributes: `role`, `aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, `aria-modal`.
- Color contrast must meet WCAG 2.1 AA (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text/UI).
- `prefers-color-scheme` and `prefers-reduced-motion` must both be supported.

## Component Patterns

- Web components use LitElement with `@customElement` decorator.
- Component names: `hu-<name>` prefix (e.g. `hu-button`, `hu-card`, `hu-modal`).
- Styles: `static styles = css\`...\`` using `--hu-*` tokens exclusively.
- Slots for composition; properties for data; events for communication upward.
- New components must have corresponding test files in `ui/src/` or `ui/tests/`.

## Responsive Breakpoints

- Standard breakpoint values: 480px (sm), 640px (md), 768px (lg), 1024px (xl) — matches `breakpoints.tokens.json`
- Every `@media (max-width: Xpx)` MUST include an annotation comment: `@media (max-width: 480px) /* --hu-breakpoint-sm */ {`
- Never add new magic-number breakpoints — use only the 4 standard values above
- Breakpoint tokens: `--hu-breakpoint-sm` (480px), `--hu-breakpoint-md` (640px), `--hu-breakpoint-lg` (768px), `--hu-breakpoint-xl` (1024px)

## Alpha Transparency (color-mix)

- **Never** use `rgba()` for transparency — use `color-mix(in srgb, var(--hu-token) XX%, transparent)`
- Fallback pattern: `var(--hu-shadow-sm, 0 2px 8px color-mix(in srgb, var(--hu-shadow-color) 10%, transparent))`
- Exception: print stylesheets may use raw values with web-specific tokens (e.g., `var(--hu-web-surface, #fff)`)

## Token Lint Enforcement

- Run `npm run lint:tokens` (in `ui/`) before any UI commit — flags raw hex, rgba, hardcoded durations, raw breakpoints
- Run `bash scripts/lint-raw-colors.sh --all` from repo root — flags raw hex colors across all `.ts` and `.css` files
- Both lints are wired into `npm run check` via `npm run lint:tokens`

## File Organization

- Shared components: `ui/src/components/`
- View pages: `ui/src/views/`
- Styles: `ui/src/styles/` (tokens generated from `design-tokens/`)
- Icons: `ui/src/icons.ts` (single source for all web dashboard icons)
- Design tokens source of truth: `design-tokens/` (W3C format)
